      "message": "With some local experiements, I found that the total execution time of                                            \ndraining the artifact channel remained the same, whichever values are                                             \nset in MaxLease, including 1 and 128.                                                                             \n                                                                                                                  \nI changes ArtifactUploader.send() to return nil immediately without                                               \nperforming the actual uploads, but the total execution of draining                                                 \nthe channel time remained the same. After additional inspections\nwith GOMAXPROCS, lsof, and strace, I found that the delays are from\nthe QPS limits, given to the channels.\n\nI removed the QPS limits, and don\u0027t worry too much about possible\nrejections by DOS config. During my tests, I experienced all outgoing\nHTTP requests got rejected, but that happened only once when I\nrepeatedly executed the test run with \u003c 1 sec interval many times.\n\nIf it becomes a visible problem, then we can tune it later, but\nI don\u0027t see if it\u0027s necessary as of this moment.\n\nBefore this patch, the total execution time was around 1m11sec, but\naround 6sec after this patch, when rdb-stream was executed with\na sample input from the Fuchsia builder.",
